#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: v2-user-type-shadows-function-ctor
description: a user case class named like a plugin functionConstructor (Money/Currency) must build as a plain Ctor, not route to the plugin companion
backends: [int]
---

# User case class wins over a plugin functionConstructor of the same name

The v2 payments bridge registers `Money`/`Currency` as `functionConstructors`
(companion factories) — the `Money` companion coerces a Decimal amount to
minor-units Long. A user who defines/imports their OWN `case class Money`
(e.g. std/money.ssc `Money(amount: Decimal, …)`) must get a plain Ctor for
THIS compile unit, not the payments companion — otherwise `Money(d, cur)`
silently mangles the amount (busi: Decimal 3000.00 → Int 300000, domain sweep
61/61 → 25/61). Fixed by `registerCaseClass` recording user case classes and
guarding the functionConstructor path against them.

```scalascript
case class Money(amount: String, currency: String)
val m = Money("3000.00", "PLN")
println(m.amount)
println(m.currency)
```
